<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 mt-16">
  <div class="text-center mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-base-content">Gender Terminology</h1>
    <p class="text-base-content/75 mt-2">A comprehensive guide to inclusive language and terminology</p>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="bg-base-200 rounded-lg shadow-md p-4 mb-6">
      <%= form.text_field :query, value: params[:query], placeholder: "Find terminology...", class: "w-full rounded-full border border-neutral-200 px-4 py-2 pl-10 text-sm focus:border-accent focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-accent dark:border-neutral-600 dark:bg-neutral-800 dark:placeholder-neutral-400", data: { action: "input->search-form#submit" } %>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Terminology Entry -->
      <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content">Gender Identity</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-2">A person's internal, deeply held sense of their gender. Unlike gender expression, gender identity is not visible to others.</p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Usage Example:</h3>
          <p class="text-base-content/70 italic mt-1">"It's important to respect someone's gender identity by using their correct pronouns and name."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Related Terms:</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-1">
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Expression</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Self-identification</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Terminology Entry -->
      <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content">Transgender</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-2">An umbrella term for people whose gender identity differs from the sex they were assigned at birth. The term transgender is not indicative of gender expression, sexual orientation, hormonal makeup, physical anatomy, or how one is perceived in daily life.</p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Usage Example:</h3>
          <p class="text-base-content/70 italic mt-1">"Some transgender people transition medically with hormones or surgeries, while others do not."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Related Terms:</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-1">
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Trans</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Transition</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Dysphoria</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Terminology Entry -->
      <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content">Non-binary</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-2">An umbrella term for people who do not identify exclusively as a man or a woman. Non-binary people may identify as being both a man and a woman, somewhere in between, or as falling completely outside these categories.</p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Usage Example:</h3>
          <p class="text-base-content/70 italic mt-1">"Many non-binary people use they/them pronouns, but some may use other pronouns or a combination of pronouns."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Related Terms:</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-1">
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Enby</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Genderqueer</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Non-conforming</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Terminology Entry -->
      <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content">Cisgender</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-2">A term used to describe a person whose gender identity aligns with the sex assigned to them at birth.</p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Usage Example:</h3>
          <p class="text-base-content/70 italic mt-1">"Using terms like 'cisgender' and 'transgender' is more inclusive than using phrases like 'biologically male/female' or 'born a man/woman'."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Related Terms:</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-1">
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Cis</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Identity</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Terminology Entry -->
      <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content">Gender Expression</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/80 mt-2">External manifestations of gender, expressed through a person's name, pronouns, clothing, haircut, behavior, voice, and/or body characteristics. Society identifies these cues as masculine and feminine, although what is considered masculine or feminine changes over time and varies by culture.</p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Usage Example:</h3>
          <p class="text-base-content/70 italic mt-1">"A person's gender expression may not align with their gender identity, and should not be used to make assumptions about their identity."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <h3 class="text-md font-medium text-base-content">Related Terms:</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-1">
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Presentation</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Performance</span>
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-base-200 text-base-content/80 rounded-full text-sm">Gender Non-conforming</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
